The paper deals with dynamic data structures for interval coloring, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves graph theory concepts such as interval graphs and cliques, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible category. The paper also discusses online algorithms, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
